<item>
            <title>[JDK-8155191] Specify that SecureRandom.nextBytes(byte[]) throws NullPointerException when byte array is null</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8155191</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Most SecureRandom implementations throw an NPE when nextBytes(null) is called, but not the one from SunPKCS11 where it&amp;#39;s silently ignored. We might want to specify and enforce at the API level that an NPE should be thrown.</description>
