Date: 2023-05-04 01:58:42 +0000</comment>
                            <comment id="14499637" author="valeriep" created="Wed, 1 Jun 2022 16:53:10 -0700"  >Agree, java.security.SecureRandom.nextBytes(byte[]) should document the NPE when &amp;#39;bytes&amp;#39; is null as in the method of the parent class (Random.nextBytes(byte[])) as well as SecureRandom.nextBytes(byte[], SecureRandomParameters). The non-null check should also be at the java.security.SecureRandom level to ensure consistent behavior across providers.</comment>
                            <comment id="13934001" author="wetmore" created="Wed, 27 Apr 2016 16:25:53 -0700"  >To be clear, there are two parts here:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
1.  API change to NPE&lt;br/&gt;
2.  Either PKCS11 or within in the SecureRandom code (preferred) must NPE on a null.</comment>
